# 1. みんなでお正月ショー

Tsukasa: “Hah hah hah hah!”
Tsukasa: “After ten years of toil, I, Tsukasanosuke Tenma, have at long last discovered the greatest treasure under the sun!”
Tsukasa: “However, this box is enormous... If it is filled with gold, then I would not have to work another day as long as I live.”
Tsukasa: “Heh heh heh. So, let us see what is inside!”
MEIKO: Now, Robo-Nene! Flash your lights!
Robo-Nene: Engaging.
Tsukasa: “Ah, such a heavenly light...! This must be a treasure of immeasurable wealth!”
Tsukasa: “Oh, my eyes... I was afraid that I had gone blind... Hm?”
Tsukasa: “Waaaaaaaaah!!! Wh-What is this?!”
Lion Dance Robot: “CHOMP CHOMP CHOMP. CHOMP CHOMP...”
Tsukasa: “Hm...?! 'Be at ease, young one'...?”
Tsukasa: “How is this possible?! All I hear is him chomping, but I can understand exactly what he is trying to say...!”
Tsukasa: “What in the world are you?!”
Lion Dance Robot: “CHOMP. CHOMP CHOMP.”
Tsukasa: “Huh?! 'I am a deity'...?! What are you saying...?”
Tsukasa: “Yes, this shrine does indeed have a long history... But to think that you are its patron deity!”
Lion Dance Robot: “CHOMP, CHOMP CHOMP CHOMP. CHOMP CHOMP CHOMP.”
Tsukasa: “Uh... 'It is understandable that you do not believe me'...? An odd and boastful creature you are...”
Lion Dance Robot: “CHOMP!”
Tsukasa: “Gwah...! His thoughts keep penetrating my head...!”
Tsukasa: “What?! 'I shall grant you a wish if you are able to make the people of this land smile'...?!”
Lion Dance Robot: “CHOMP.”
Tsukasa: “A-Anything...? Including gold, money and giant castles...?!”
Lion Dance Robot: “CHOMP! CHOMP...!”
MEIKO: One more time, Robo-Nene!
KAITO: Miku, Len, just like we practiced! Get ready to raise the castle backdrop on three! One, two, three!
Miku & Len: Now!
Tsukasa: “Wh-What?! A castle just appeared in the distance?! You truly are a deity...?”
Tsukasa: “Then, I know! To make my dream of having a castle of my own a reality, I shall make the people of this land smile...”
Lion Dance Robot: “CHOMP!”
Luka: And so, Tsukasanosuke embarked on a journey with the Lion Dance Deity to perform for people all across Japan♪
Emu: “Woof woof woof! It's great to see so many people visiting the shrine today♪”
Emu: “But this Lion-Dog's starting to get bored of being stuck here working. It'd be great to go out for a walk and go somewhere else for a change...”
Tsukasa: “Come one, come all! All are welcome to see the traveling performer!”
Emu: “Hm? Is he a traveling performer? Does that mean he's gonna do something for all of us?”
Emu: “That sounds fun! Oh, I know! I should ask to see if I can join him...!”
Nene: “*Yawn* Another beautiful day...”
Nene: “I am so glad that I was born a Snake Deity. All these humans bring me offerings without me having to lift a finger.”
Nene: “However, they are all so scared of me that they refuse to stay to listen to my singing... *Sigh*”
Tsukasa: “Come one, come all!”
Emu: “See the traveling performer's amazing show! Woof woof! Huh...?”
Emu: “Hey, Tsukasanosuke! I see a Snake Deity over there!”
Tsukasa: “A Snake Deity?! That is quite a rare find... Hm...?”
Tsukasa: “Hehehe... If she were to join us, our performance should attract just that much more attention! Lion-Dog, we must capture her!”
Emu: “Yeah!”
Nene: “Wh-What?! Capture?! N-No, stay away!”
Rui: “Oh, what is this? I exited the shrine to see what was going on with the village...”
Emu: “Come one, come all! See the traveling performer's amazing show!”
Nene: “S-Singing is all I promised to do...!”
Rui: “Well, it is nice to see a troupe like this for a change.”
Rui: “It may actually be worth this shapeshifting fox's time to join in on the festivities.”
Rui: “Let us see how it goes... Hello there, traveling performer. Do you have a moment?”
Tsukasa: “Hm?”
Luka: The Lion Dance Deity led the human, Lion-Dog, Snake and Fox as they set out to put smiles on the faces of people all across Japan, from north to south, by performing a show that they had never seen before.
Luka: Before they knew it, ten years had passed, and they were able to put on a New Year's performance that made the entire audience smile from ear to ear.
Tsukasa: “We... We finally did it...!”
Lion Dance Robot: “CHOMP CHOMP.”
Tsukasa: “Hah hah hah! You can say that again! I, Tsukasanosuke, am the most dashing man in all of Japan after all!”
Tsukasa: “Now, my divine friend! I believe it is time for you to grant me my wish!”
Tsukasa: “First, my castle! Naturally, I shall call it, Tenma Castle!”
Lion Dance Robot: “CHOMP...”
Tsukasa: “Huh...?!”
Emu: “What do you mean, 'I cannot'...?”
Lion Dance Robot: “CHOMP CHOMP CHOMP...”
Nene: “What...? 'Despite being a deity, my powers waned significantly while I was sealed away, so I am limited to producing projections of castles'...?”
Tsukasa: “Wh-What is the meaning of this...?! I had your word. It is why I worked so hard all these years! Was it all a lie?!”
Lion Dance Robot: “CHOMP...”
Tsukasa: “Bah... You liar! Begone with you...!”
Emu: “Wait, no! Don't go!”
Lion Dance Robot: “CHOMP...”
Tsukasa: “*Sob* Were these past ten years all for naught...?”
Emu: “Please cheer up, Tsukasanosuke! Your castle... I can't really do anything about that...”
Emu: “But I had a lot of fun these past ten years thanks to you.”
Tsukasa: “So what if you did...? You had fun. Good for you. But I have nothing to show for my efforts...”
Nene: “Are you sure?”
Nene: “I have been alive for 200 years, but these past ten years have definitely been the most fun...”
Nene: “All good things eventually wither away. Castles are no exception. However, the time we spent together... That will likely never fade.”
Rui: “Yes, I agree. I too have been alive for quite some time...”
Rui: “But I would not trade seeing people all across Japan smile for any amount of gold.”
Rui: “Tsukasanosuke, you may not have been rewarded with a physical treasure. However, to those who you've made smile, you mean everything to them...”
Rui: “And those smiles we saw... That became our treasure.”
Tsukasa: “Their smiles are our treasure...? I see...”
Tsukasa: “And yet, we still have one person left who is not smiling... Well, a deity, not a person...”
Lion Dance Robot: “CHOMP...”
Tsukasa: “... I apologize for calling you a liar, my friend.”
Tsukasa: “I could not have attained this treasure on my own. You were the one who made it possible.”
Tsukasa: “So, thank you for these past ten years.”
Lion Dance Robot: “...! CHOMP!”
Tsukasa: “Huh?! Why are you glowing...?!”
Lion Dance Robot: “CHOMP! CHOMP CHOMP!”
Rui: “I see. I do not fully understand what is happening, but by bringing back the smiles on everyone's faces, you seem to have regained your powers...”
Nene: “So much power...! More power than even the Great Snake Deity!”
Tsukasa: “W-Wait! A real castle...?! My wish came true...?”
Emu: “That's great, Tsukasanosuke! You finally got the castle you wanted!”
Tsukasa: “How would you all feel about using this place as a theatre for our performances...?”
Tsukasa: “We can gather people here to do performances for them, and even perform outside from time to time... Would that not be a fun way to put a smile on the faces of the people of this land?”
Emu: “Yeah! I wanna do that! Let's keep doing shows together!”
Lion Dance Robot: “CHOMP!”
Tsukasa: “Whoa! Give me a little warning before throwing yourselves at me like that! Hahaha...!”
Luka: And so, Tsukasanosuke and his merry group of friends continued to make everybody all across the land smile. The end.
KAITO: Yes, excellent dress rehearsal...! And a wonderful New Year's spectacle!
Tsukasa: Hah hah hah! Of course it is!
Rui: We plan to have some members of the audience participate during the day of, so things should become even more fun.
Miku: The audience?! That does sound like fun♪ Break a leg, you guys☆
Nene: Thanks. Still, it's been pretty long since we last properly did a show at the Wonder Stage...
Emu: Yeah, it has! As sad as it was to hear that we wouldn't be doing any more ambassadorial performances...
Emu: Let's do our best to make everyone who comes to visit the Wonder Stage smile from ear to ear!
Tsukasa: (No more ambassadorial performances...)
Luka: Hm? Is everything okay, Tsukasa...? You look like you have something on your mind...
Tsukasa: Hm? Me? No, I'm okay. It's nothing...
Lion Dance Robot: CHOMP...! CHOMP CHOMP! CHOMP...!
Tsukasa: Hm? Wh-What the...? Why is smoke coming out of Lion Dance Robot all of a sudden...?
Rui: Oh, he may be overheating because he had to move around quite a lot just now... Which means he might...
Lion Dance Robot: CHOMP!!!
Tsukasa: Waaah! Wh-Why's he chasing after me again?!
Rui: Don't worry. I made it so his fans automatically cool him while he runs around. He isn't malfunctioning, so he should settle down in a moment.
Tsukasa: Wait, so I have to keep running until he does?!
Rin: Oh, they're playing tag♪ We wanna join!
Len: Alright, let's jump right into it!
Tsukasa: W-Wait! We aren't playing tag!!!
